dcterms:description: In this environment, an agent navigates a gridworld to reach as many targets as possible within a given time limit, incentivized to reach targets placed randomly in a 10 × 10 grid.
dcterms:title: Navigation problem

dcterms:description: The Traveling Salesman Problem (TSP) involves finding the shortest route that visits each city once and returns to the starting city, with applications in logistics and planning.
dcterms:title: Traveling salesman problem (TSP)

dcterms:description: The Vertex k-center problem (VKCP) involves selecting a subset of points to minimize the maximum distance from any point to its nearest selected point, with applications in facility location.
dcterms:title: Vertex k-center problem (VKCP)

dcterms:creator: Fred Glover
Ching-Chung Kuo

dcterms:description: The Maximum Diversity Problem (MDP) involves selecting a subset of points to maximize the minimum distance between distinct points, with applications in various fields including ecology and telecommunications.
dcterms:title: Maximum diversity problem (MDP)

dcterms:creator: Andreas Junghanns

dcterms:description: Sokoban is a puzzle where an agent pushes boxes around a warehouse to get them to storage locations, requiring planning and strategy to avoid getting stuck.
